The paper deals with automatic image tagging, which is a problem in computer vision and multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed solution involves using acoustic sensing on mobile phones, which could also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SD). The paper also addresses the challenge of correlating name tags with corresponding people in the picture, which could be related to systems and control (cs.SY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
